        <abstract> 
<p>Two correspondents report fertilising <hi rend="italic">Vinca rosea</hi> by imitating the action of an insect inserting its proboscis. Another says his <hi rend="italic">Vinca rosea</hi> seed profusely without artificial fertilisation. CD asks what might explain the difference in results. In the latter instance, are the plants kept in a greenhouse with windows left open, so that moths could get access at night?</p> 
        </abstract>
